How does a program read the cvMat object, in particular, what is the
order of the pixel structure?
Anser: In the program, the cvMat represent a images bvy a Matrix. In the Matrix, every pixel is represented by the(rows,cloumns).
And there is also a index following to represent the numbers of channels. Colorful RGB images have 3 channels, they are blue(2), 
green(1) and red(0).
